text:
Food (5/5): ordered the Sup Kambing ribs (big $10) and roti/ bread ($1). Gravy was spicy and packed with flavour. Mutton was tender but not mushy. Delicious. Perfect meal especially on a rainy day.

Service (3/5): satisfactory.

Atmosphere (5/5): well ventilated and clean hawker centre. Ample seating.

Highly recommended.

p.s. wasnâ€™t expecting to be blown away so no photos!
Nice for nasi goreng pattaya with $7.

The stir fried rice, bee hoon and noodles are consistently great in terms of flavour, vegetable content, and spice level. And you can make special requests too. I like the use of the coriander on the dishes they make.
